article.headline: Utah St. 66, San Jose St. 57
article.story: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -- Stephen DuCharme scored 19 points to lead four Utah State players in double figures as the Aggies beat San Jose State 66-57 Saturday night. Durrall Peterson scored 13 and Chaz Spicer added 12 points for Utah State (16-7, 5-4 Western Athletic Conference) and Jaycee Carroll scored 11. The Spartans (3-19, 2-8 WAC) were led by Carlton Spencer, Tim Pierce and Menelik Barbary with 13 apiece. Jamon Hill added 11 points for San Jose State. The Aggies led 48-38 with 11:20 left in the second half, but full-court pressure by the Spartans rattled the Aggies and cut the lead to 55-53 with 5:20 to play. USU then settled down and finished the game with an 11-4 run. The Spartans were credited with 10 steals while USU had 14 turnovers in the game. In the opening half, USU led most of the way, taking a 26-17 lead with 3:58 remaining. The Spartans then went on a 13-0 run to take the lead and were up 30-29 at halftime.
